Merge pull request #11 from rurban/master

Fix perl warning

Fix perl warning

- Unescaped left brace in regex is deprecated here (and will be fatal in
  Perl 5.30), passed through in regex; marked by <-- HERE in m/(\w){ <--
  HERE / at /usr/bin/abi-dumper line 3200.
Release 1.1
Deny analysis of static libraries.

- Compress ABI dumps before writing to drive from RAM
- Fixed analysis of inline functions (WARNING: old dumps should be regenerated before comparing by ABICC)
- Bumped ABI dump version

- Added -ld-library-path option to specify paths to add to LD_LIBRARY_PATH variable before executing vtable-dumper
- Improved search for header files
- Carefully handle lexical blocks
- Fixed detection of a function header file
- Fixed detection of inline functions
Fixed analysis of templated unions. Fixed InLine property. Fixed detection of parameters. Minimal support for lambda expressions. Added -lambda option.
Fixed analysis of typedefs.
Fixed analysis of zero-size structs. Fixed -public-headers option. Fixed analysis of global data.
Fixed template type names. Detecting public typedefs.
Detection of symbols in header files missed by Ctags. Fixed -public-headers option. Fixed analysis of templates. Fixed analysis of anon data types.

Reduced RAM usage on large compressed debug info. Added -ctags-def option. Added -all-units option. Support for unspecified_type. Fixed analysis of symbol versions. Removed duplicates from ABI dump. Code cleaning.
Up to 4 times less RAM usage. Fixed 'Copied' attribute of a class. Code cleaning.
Fixed -public-headers option. Added -include-defines option. Fixed parameter offsets in the ABI dump. Fixed selection of header files for functions. More debug messages.
Fixed template type names.
